whole box and dice, the
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:everything; `the whole works'
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:cf. whole shooting-box, the
Pronunciation:
Notes: check SND; ca1940 Havelock; cf. also the whole kit and cabood; ca1946 R. Mason, who suggests it may arise from shopkeeper's idiom, one out of the box in contrast with one on the shelf, shop-soiled: cf (one) out of the drawer
